Johannesburg - Rising talent Pascal Kubayi, affectionately known as DJ Pasca, speaks candidly about his music journey, all life highlights and his latest music offering. After working tirelessly to ensure that his EP titled Nwana Mhani came to life, DJ Pasca could not stop brimming with pride while unpacking interesting details about it. Having released it successfully he revealed he has never been more eager to do more music. Kubayi shared that he has always wanted to use his love for music as a vessel to carry content that is thought-provoking and inspiring. Growing up in an environment where music was among many things respected by his loved ones played a significant role in the artist he is today. Speaking with the Star news the rising star said his music was inspired by all the struggles that he had encountered in his life. “I did not get where I am right now by being spoon-fed or being given anything. My story, my family, and all that I have been through inspire me. Mostly taking care of my sisters.” Though at times life problems would be pulling him back DJ Pasca said his passion for the art helped him overcome the challenges. He detailed the support demonstrated by people after dropping his EP serves as one of his proudest moments. He also mentioned the ability to support his sister after losing their mother years ago. When they ask for assistance he feels the need to always deliver for them. He hopes that his music garners all the attention it deserves and reaches great heights “I am honestly looking for greater things after this EP. I want to make it. I would like to come through with new sounds. I got influenced by other celebrities. I feel like it’s time for me to influence as well. Everything that I have gained. The knowledge that I have gained. I want my name to be known. And change the world.”